{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place meat pieces into mixing bowl and mince <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> <strong>.<\/strong> Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place mixed roots and vegetables and fresh mixed herbs into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add rock salt, red wine, bay leaf, whole clove and reserved minced meat. Cook <nobr>25 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid. Mixture will thicken and become fairly dry.","Remove simmering basket, <strong>insert measuring cup<\/strong> and blend <nobr>1 min\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer into an airtight container and allow to cool before using or storing in the refrigerator."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["300 g meat pieces, sinew free, cut into pieces, partially frozen","300 g mixed roots and vegetables (e.g. celery stalk, carrots, onions, garlic, tomatoes), cut into pieces as needed","4 sprigs fresh mixed herbs (e.g. sage, rosemary), leaves only","150 g rock salt","120 g red wine","1 dried bay leaf","1 whole clove"]}],"id":"r67058","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-b1IPAuaQ7GI\/XZaqNnk5s1I\/AAAAAAAAhaU\/X8gCbQyAR4E1Eqc8pyNQYThWn83XyTgRgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_RckGl5OihGjd1qHH.png","title":"Meat stock paste","publishedAt":"2014-09-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.7 g","fat":"0.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"0.6 g","calories":"87 kJ \/ 21 kcal"},"usefulItems":"airtight container, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["1 tbsp stock paste is roughly equivalent to 1 shop-bought meat stock cube.","To make meat stock, use 1 tbsp per 500 g water.","Stock paste keeps in the refrigerator for several months.","The salt in this recipe is used as the preservation agent. When mixed with water as described above, the stock does not taste too salty.","If you wish to decrease the salt in the recipe, we recommend you store the stock paste in the freezer.","Small quantities of sea vegetables, such as dulse, wakame or kombu, can be added to the stock for extra flavour and nutrients.","Use a mixture of red and white wine for this recipe if desired.","Adapt this recipe using leftover vegetables you have in your refrigerator. Weigh what you have into the mixing bowl to ensure what you have is consistent with the recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","480 g"]}